text:
Ordered "dough skin soup", 面片汤and steamed dumplings.

Very unique dough skin soup! First time seeing this in Singapore. Cost $5. Thick generous egg soup. no meat inside, but the handmade dough is worth the try.

10 dumplings for $7. Acceptable also.

But minus one star for using disposable cutleries even for dine-in.

Recommended for people who dont mind :)

Super juicy and yummy!
Thumb up👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼
Give it a try if u are around here!

Must try the dough skin soup. Very unique dish that tastes like Thai suki. The eggy soup broth is very smooth and comforting but the bits of hae bee(dried shrimp) at the bottom of the bowl is quite irritating.

The pan fried dumplings were disappointing. It tasted like they were baked instead of fried - so hard and dry.

Breakfast on 30 March 2024
Stall No. 12: Tian Jin Fong Kee 天津冯记
Location: Serangoon Garden Food Centre, the whole place is spacious and cooling with lots of fans for ventilation.

Ordered Zhajiang Noodles 炸酱面 $4 & Steamed Pork Dumplings 10pcs at $7
Verdict: 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
Comments: Noodles texture very nice, sauce just nice and the meat in the sauce tastes great. Dumplings were tasty and juicy.
Their both steam and fried dumplings are extremely delicious! The dough is soft and smooth. A must try if u are nearby oh!
